
pip freeze --> will show all the installed packages for the env
pytest and pytest-cov have been installed as well

just running pytest on venv will run all tests

# will show the percentage of the code covered through tests 'guess' is a directory
pytest --cov-report term-missing --cov='guess'

# the dot can be used when we run it from the current directory
pytest --cov-report term-missing --cov='.'

#capfd --> (Capture Output Printed By Your Programm) --  will allow to see what is being prompted
#to the user in console (feedback sent by the input)